Since your hours can exceed 24, you can&#39;t use `strtotime` based methods to convert them. One way to do the math is to explode each value on `:` to separate the hours and minutes and sum the total minutes. You can then compute the average minutes and output that in the required format:

    $total_minutes = 0;
    foreach ($times as $time) {
        list($hours, $minutes) = explode(&#39;:&#39;, $time);
        $total_minutes += $hours * 60 + $minutes;
    }
    $average_minutes = $total_minutes / count($times);
    echo &quot;Average time is &quot; . round($average_minutes / 60, 2) . &quot; hour\n&quot;;
    $average_hours = floor($average_minutes / 60);
    $average_minutes = $average_minutes % 60;
